div.div: How do you have an event go every hour in roblox?

If you simply want a `wait` statement and know how you want to do this with your loop already programmed, a `wait` statement lasting an hour is `wait(3600)`. Otherwise, here are some loop solutions that run code every hour according to the game or according to a time zone. To run the script when the game starts, then do something every hour since then: ```lua while wait(3600) do -- this should be the code that runs every hour end ```
To run according to UST (every time the minutes hit 0 in universal standard time): ```lua while wait(1) do local timeTable = os.date("!*t", tick()) if timeTable["min"] == "00" then -- this should be the code that runs every hour end end ```
To run according to the local time zone (this only works in localscripts to my knowledge): ```lua while wait(1) do if os.date("%M", os.time()) == "00" then print("Running on "..os.date("%Z", os.time().."'s local time.") -- this should be the code that runs every hour end end ```
If you're new to scripting and unsure which to pick, do either the first or the third.
